'''Hizdahr zo Loraq''' is a recurring character in the [[Season 4|fourth]] and [[Season 5|fifth]] seasons. He is played by [[Joel Fry]] and debuts in &quot;[[Breaker of Chains]]&quot;. He is a formerÂ [[Slavery|slave-trader]] from the city of [[Meereen]], on the coast of [[Slaver's Bay]], and a scion of the [[House of Loraq]], an ancient and proud line of slavers.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Laws of Gods and Men]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Hizdahr belongs to the ancient aristocratic House of Loraq, who have been one of the ruling families of [[Great Masters|slavemasters]] in Meereen for many generations.

Hizdahr zo Loraq is fluent in the [[Common Tongue]] of Westeros, which is not unusual for merchants in Essos, as they take part in long-distance trade.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Laws of Gods and Men]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Hizdahr zo Loraq is the son of one of the many [[Great Masters]]. He, along with his father and the rest of Meereen's nobility,Â gather over the walls of the city when [[Daenerys Targaryen]] and her army appear before the city gates to lay [[Siege of Meereen|siege]] to it.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Breaker of Chains]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

His father is crucified in the aftermath of the siege, a matter which he later confronts her about personally. Hizdahr pleads to be allowed to bury him at the [[Temple of the Graces]], to which she agrees, after learning that he had opposed the crucifixion of the slave children as an ill-conceived warning against Daenerys.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Laws of Gods and Men]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Some weeks later, Daenerys tells [[Jorah Mormont]] to send Hizdahr to [[Yunkai]] as her ambassador. Hizdahr is to offer the [[Wise Masters]] a choice: they can &quot;live in her new world&quot; and accept the abolition of slavery, or &quot;die in their old one&quot; at the hands of the [[Second Sons (mercenary company)|Second Sons]] sent under the command of [[Daario Naharis]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Mockingbird]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
